America's Got Talent runner-up the Ndlovu Youth Choir is excited to welcome the 2019 Rugby World Cup (RWC) champions at Johannesburg's OR Tambo International Airport on today. READ: SPRINGBOKS ARE WORLD CHAMPIONS! The Springboks are due to arrive in SA from Japan on Tuesday and Wednesday. Springboks Captain, Siya Kolisi and team coach Rassie Erasmus are set to address the media after their arrival. Ndlovu Youth Choir took to Twitter to announce that they will be welcoming the champions. “Join us in giving our World Champions the welcome they deserve,” the choir wrote.  